'''''All the Devils Are Here: The Hidden History of the Financial Crisis''''' is a nonfiction [[book]] by [[author]]s [[Bethany McLean]] and [[Joseph Nocera]] the [[Financial crisis of 2007â2010|2008 financial crisis]]. It details account of how the financial crisis bubbled up from a volatile, and bipartisan, mixture of government meddling and ''[[laissez-faire]]''. It concludes it was not an accident, that banks understood the big picture before the crisis happened but continued with bad practices.
== The Title == The title of the book comes from [[The Tempest]], a [[William Shakespeare]] play in which he wrote "Hell is empty, and all the devils are here."
